EKS shared clusters access
==========================

This VM contains EKS cluster information generated from Terraform outputs:
- /home/{{ ansible_hostname }}/.kube/config.eks
- alias shell: eks='kubectl --kubeconfig /home/{{ ansible_hostname }}/.kube/config.eks'

Usage examples:
1) List available contexts:
   eks config get-contexts

2) Query nodes using default context from config.eks (cluster00):
   eks get nodes

3) Query nodes on another context:
   eks --context cluster01 get nodes

Notes:
- Default context is cluster00 in /home/{{ ansible_hostname }}/.kube/config.eks.
- The kubeconfig uses AWS CLI exec authentication (aws eks get-token).
- You need valid AWS credentials and permissions for the target EKS clusters.
